f outside friends. Of course some. Also - because we were six - months of the year abroad you see, so that almost - split - split us up. And abroad - Bordighera - I don't - we didn't seem to have - somebody came for a visit - local friends there - there w
a
s a rather - famous character who - you know the writer George MacDonald? He lived there and was sort of - oracle to some people and a crank to others you know. And he had - this - household of - adopted children. We used to know some of them. I forget if
 he'd had children of his own but there was a great thing about adoption when not adopted oneself.
