es. Her mother died when she was seven, and her - father - and she was, I think seventeen, and they were a family of - thirteen - all brought up by the oldest sister who was - from when she was eighteen I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1054659 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Did you know her, your oldest aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5195713 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Yes, she's - Lady Pembroke, and - as I say nine brothers, so it was rather a lot - of unruly - wild boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1054659 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 What a tremendous responsibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5195713 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1054659 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Did your father ever have any work for which he got a salary?
