 - we were allowed to go together, my eldest - I think - to a smallish dance, I think it rather depended what sort of dance. I think if it was a very - big grand one - it might have had to have been - a real chap - you know, a real chaperone, and then the
r
e were ones who - adored lighted candles and undertook - to take - look after lots of girls. As my mother hated going out - I was - generally under the care of somebody like that. And some relations, I mean - some - slightly older - cousins. Men cousins w
ere allowed - to - look after one too. Yes. Yes. And they were rather - they used to rather keep a - blind eye on - how many times one dances so one rather liked - liked to be under their charge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1054659 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 They were sort of easier going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5195713 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Yes, I mean I'd an - older cousin called - Cl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15945211\charrsid12720898 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
