hter you see, so that one sat - near an old person at dinner very often, because you'd got the - as I say the host.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1054659 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Did those bother you, would you have liked sometimes to have had rather younger
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5195713 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Yes it did rather depend on really who the host w
as. And also as I say you started if it was - dinner for a dance, you started - one partner short, you see. You know, 'cos - they were sitting - whoever you sat next - were supposed in duty bound to ask you whether he was a friend or not you know, so supp
osing you went to a dance where you didn't know many people - you were one short if you - sat next to the host. But in certain cases one looked forward to sitting next to the host, I used to dine quite a lot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15945211\charrsid12720898  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 with - the Wenyss' and - the Lord Wenyss at that 
time. Was - always frightfully amusing. I mean he remained a friend of my husband's afterwards un - until - oh until - the war, yes after the war, and he was very very amusing so - I liked sitting next to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1054659 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Do you remember paying calls on people with cards?
