BLANK\}
 who was - at the time of Freddie the Great, when there was tremendous - correspondence - from Prussia. He had - I think he was - Secretary of State or something, - that Lord Holderness, I suppose that one could find in a - in a - Debrett. And they w
ere very interesting - letters. A lot - all those manuscripts kept there, and nobody had - paid any attention to them I remember in those days - at all. And we had rather fun going through them, I was doing - time of Queen Anne and so, and this tutor, so 
