e looked up everything - all the - letters and things of interest there. And then the - most - valuable books were kept there too. There was a wonderful - illuminated Chaucer - that was very valuable and a - first folio Shakespeare. Those sort of - things
 were kept in the muniment room that I remember. And I think now they're all - somewhere - in - I'm not sure if it's - somewhere in York - stored, they haven't been able to go through all the papers yet. By way of doing it sometime.
