\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1054659 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 But you always all had your own beds did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5195713 ML  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 Yes. But I think she an
d I slept together - in quite a lot of places, 'cos I remember a summer in London - when we were sent to bed - you know, sent to bed so early - in those days and with the light - full off you know, full daylight and all - one hated it and one knew one cou
l
dn't sleep for ages - rooms I suppose - it was so hot - in hot weather, for children, and we invented various - ways of amusing ourselves when we'd been sent to bed. And one by one they were trampled on. One was - to dance - to barrel organs. Which we ado
red. Barrel organ - grea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1012224\charrsid12720898 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2701124\charrsid12720898 
 luck - bit of luck, barrel organ came round. So then we danced madly to that, but of course they heard us and came and stopped that. Then we invented a steeplechase course - from one bed - bed to another, but in time that was heard
